@{
PrintOut (SomeValue());
@}

  /*********************************************/

PrintOut (a)           /* Print the value */

int a;

@{
printf ("%d",a);
@}

  /**********************************************/

SomeValue ()     /* Return an arbitrary number */

@{
return (42);
@}

@end smallexample
@noindent
This often gives a concise way of passing a value to a function.

